commit.message:
Fix poptCallbackType documentation.

Issue #87
Honor ENABLE_WERROR for Doxygen too
Add minimal docs to everything in popt.h
popt's alias nesting depth is an internal constant

Use cmake's Doxygen integration, only generate docs for public API

API docs are meant for API consumers, spilling out popt internals
is not helpful for that case, on the contrary.

Cmake has integrated Doxygen support, might as well use it. Buys us
a free time-stamping mode to make builds sane again.
Add options for building with address and undefined behavior sanitizers
Bump CI to Fedora 39, 36 is getting a bit long in the tooth
Add build option to enable -Werror, use in CI
Restore -Wall as the project default compile warning level

man-page: Improve example

Changes following:
  - Free memory in usage().
  - Use POPT_TABLEEND macro when creating option table.
  - Use POPT_ARG_NONE instead of magic number in option table.
  - Cast 'argv' to const, fixes incompatible pointer warning.
  - Remove end-of-line whitespace.
  - Call usage() if to few command-line arguments.
man-page: Add information for flags used in poptGetContext()

Add GitHub workflow file

This replaces our Semaphore CI setup.

src/CMakeLists.txt: link to iconv only if it has been found

fixes compilation when iconv is missing / not detected by cmake

the relevant code is already properly guarded by ifdefs

cmake: Fix check for vasprintf

This fixes the check by changing stdio to stdio.h

Split off translations to a separate project

With Weblate managing our translations, carrying them does nothing but
create conflicts and annoyances of various kinds. Besides, the
translation updates are nothing but an annoyance in the git history.
Translators deserve credit for their work as much as anyone, but the
code history is the wrong place for that. As a nice side-effect, this
effectively prevents people from filing PR's for translation updates which
we can't process anyway.

The translations now live at a separate repository at
https://github.com/rpm-software-management/popt-l10n, integration with
dist tarball creation and source string scanning to be done. For now,
just skip the po/ directory if translations are not present.

Fixes: #93

cmake: Fix another typo in pkgconfig file template

Make sure all variables uses {} and not ()

cmake: Fix typo in pkgconfig file template

CMAKE_INSTAL_INCLUDEDIR --> CMAKE_INSTALL_INCLUDEDIR
This fixes path defined for includedir variable

cmake: Add check for iconv support

popt can optionally use iconv to support an expanded set of encodings,
so we should detect and enable this when available.

cmake: Search for sh instead of bash

We only need POSIX sh for the test suite. While bash(1) is guaranteed
to be a compatible Bourne shell, we probably can assume that sh(1)
is too on any system.

Drop superfluous const in function declaration

The parameter error is of type `int`, which is passed by value.

Use string literal as format string

    popthelp.c:463:34: warning: format not a string literal, argument types not checked [-Wformat-nonliteral]
      463 |                 POPT_fprintf(fp, format, fmthelp, " ");
          |                                  ^~~~~~
Remove autotools build system
Switch CI to CMake
Initial CMake build system
Fix multiple typos in comments

tests: Fix reporting of test failures

After commit a4afb898f7758160acda71d774c7d98d528da273 the testsuite
no longer reported test failures. This is because we rely on the exit
status code of the script, and currently, this is always 0.

If any test fails, we will exit with status code 2. The entire testsuite
will continue to run, even after a test has failed.
